  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Process Engineer (East)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Lead a team of process engineers and technicians to optimize production efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with internal departments to establish a streamlined process operation flow aligned with customer and business requirements.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper maintenance of production work instructions, including SFC control and SAP processes.</li>\n  <li>Oversee engineering change order (ECO) implementations and operational adjustments.</li>\n  <li>Drive process efficiency through continuous improvements, UPH tracking, and Kaizen activities.</li>\n  <li>Update and track the engineering change (EC) master list.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and maintain accurate working instructions.</li>\n  <li>Conduct training sessions on work instructions for production staff.</li>\n  <li>Support the new product introduction (NPI) process.</li>\n  <li>Assist in mass production runs.</li>\n  <li>Participate in ISO implementation and maintenance activities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
